01:52:40,448 --> 01:52:43,417
They don't have pensions
in my line of work.

1402
01:52:43,751 --> 01:52:45,651
And the software does
what it's supposed to do.

1403
01:52:45,753 --> 01:52:49,655
And I been chasing Micky Rosa
around here for too damn long.

1404
01:52:50,892 --> 01:52:53,156
I'm looking at
some retirement.

1405
01:52:55,063 --> 01:52:56,530
Leave the bag.

1406
01:52:58,600 --> 01:53:00,898
No. No, no, no, no.

1407
01:53:01,002 --> 01:53:05,496
I need this money. You have no idea
what I went through to get this money.

1408
01:53:05,607 --> 01:53:10,601
I know, kid, but you're gonna figure out
how to get everything you want in this life,

1409
01:53:10,712 --> 01:53:12,441
'cause you're smart.

1410
01:53:14,015 --> 01:53:18,543
So, you're gonna
leave the bag.

1411
01:53:23,591 --> 01:53:28,187
Ben, give him the bag. Give him the bag.
It doesn't matter. Give him the bag.

1412
01:53:37,038 --> 01:53:38,835
I knew you were smart.

1413
01:53:57,692 --> 01:54:00,422
<i>I had a 1590 on my SAT.</i>

1414
01:54:00,528 --> 01:54:02,587
<i>I got a 44 on my MCATs.</i>

1415
01:54:03,097 --> 01:54:06,225
<i>And I have
a 4.0 GPA from MIT.</i>

1416
01:54:06,334 --> 01:54:08,802
<i>I thought I had
my life mapped out.</i>

1417
01:54:10,705 --> 01:54:11,797
<i>But then I remembered</i>

1418
01:54:11,906 --> 01:54:15,364
<i>what my Nonlinear Equations
professor once told me,</i>

1419
01:54:15,910 --> 01:54:19,141
<i>"Always account
for variable change."</i>

1420
01:54:20,949 --> 01:54:22,473
Hello, Micky.

1421
01:54:24,185 --> 01:54:26,016
Look, I got money in Boston.
A hundred grand.

1422
01:54:26,120 --> 01:54:28,145
I'll give it to you.
Just let me walk away. I'll walk away.

1423
01:54:28,256 --> 01:54:31,316
I don't want your money,
Micky. I don't need it.

1424
01:54:37,131 --> 01:54:39,929
But I know someone
who might be interested.

1425
01:54:40,301 --> 01:54:44,397
He's good with numbers, too.
He works for the IRS.

1426
01:54:53,214 --> 01:54:55,273
<i>I let down my good friends.</i>

1427
01:54:55,950 --> 01:55:00,887
<i>But as it turns out, they weren't
too bad at simple math either.</i>

1428
01:55:26,714 --> 01:55:29,274
<i>I scored the prettiest girl
in school.</i>

1429
01:55:32,754 --> 01:55:35,382
<i>I got beaten down
by an old-school Vegas thug</i>

1430
01:55:35,490 --> 01:55:38,687
<i>who was having trouble
accepting his retirement.</i>

1431
01:55:39,994 --> 01:55:43,760
<i>But I worked out a deal with him
that got him a nice pension.</i>

1432
01:55:47,135 --> 01:55:49,933
<i>And... I lied to my mother.</i>

1433
01:55:50,405 --> 01:55:54,102
<i>But I confessed the lie,
and, well, she still loved me.</i>

1434
01:56:10,625 --> 01:56:13,890
<i>So, my senior year of college,
I joined this team.</i>

1435
01:56:14,295 --> 01:56:16,456
<i>And I learned
this new skill.</i>

1436
01:56:16,698 --> 01:56:19,724
<i>I went to Vegas
17 times to use it.</i>

1437
01:56:21,903 --> 01:56:25,430
<i>I made hundreds of thousands
of dollars counting cards.</i>

1438
01:56:26,474 --> 01:56:29,034
And then I had it all stolen from me.

1439
01:56:29,977 --> 01:56:31,137
Twice.

1440
01:56:32,447 --> 01:56:36,543
How's that for life experience,
professor? Did I dazzle you?

1441
01:56:37,719 --> 01:56:40,557
Did I... jump off the page?

